  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nFrom @ciaranmcveigh in Discord\r\n\r\n> for distributed validators it's important that the signed contents are the same across all \"co-validators\",  time.now  is likely to never match across multiple validators (the resolution on other validator clients so far has been to include a -builder-timestamp-override flag that enables the user to hardcode a value, this value is then used for every subsequent re-registration, to update the the registration config the co validators need to communicate the changes and reboot the system with the new timestamp)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
